## `test_many_rapid_ops_no_corruption(fresh_fs)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-crash-8 -->

### Purpose
Sanity: a tight loop of 1000 mixed ops in a single test run doesn't corrupt the DB. Pure library-layer stress, no subprocess. Trace covers the representative ops via sub-specs.

### Postconditions

```python
with fresh_fs.as_user(0, 0):
    for i in range(1000):
        fd = fresh_fs.create(f"/f{i}")
        fresh_fs.write(fd, str(i).encode() * 10, offset=0)
        fresh_fs.close_fd(fd)
        if i % 10 == 0:
            fresh_fs.unlink(f"/f{i}")

report = fresh_fs.fsck()
assert report.integrity_check_result == "ok"
assert report.issues == []
```

