## `test_half_written_chunk_recovers(crashable_db)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-crash-9 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: subprocess + SIGKILL sequence. Atomicity-within-transaction part IS traceable. -->

### Purpose
Starting a multi-chunk write, SIGKILL mid-write — the resulting file either has none of the write or all of it. We do not expose "written through chunk 3 but not chunk 4" to callers.

### Postconditions

```python
# 3-chunk write: straddles chunks 0, 1, 2.
crashable_db.spawn()
crashable_db.send("write-multi /big 200000", wait_ack=False)   # 200 KB spans 3+ chunks
time.sleep(0.01)
crashable_db.sigkill()

fs = crashable_db.reopen()
with fs.as_user(0, 0):
    if fs.exists("/big"):
        st = fs.stat("/big")
        # Either the full 200000 bytes, or 0 bytes (if the worker created the
        # inode but the write transaction didn't commit). No middle state.
        assert st.size in (0, 200_000)
fs.close()
```

